   <h2> What is Gastona</h2>

   <p>
      Gastona is an open source scripting language for quick development of applications.
      It is available in Windows, Linux, Raspberry Pi for desktop applications
      and as Android App. This means that it is possible to write a gastona script and run
      it in all this platforms without any modification.
   </p>

   <h2> Is Gastona different ?</h2>

   <p>
      A main design goal of Gastona is to minimize as much as possible the programming effort when
      creating applications. For example the simplistic idea "a button is a button" applies
      when building the a Graphic User Interface (GUI). Also the commands try to be as much "high level"
      as possible to do more with less.
   </p>

   <p>
      This pragmatic approach makes that gastona scripts does not look like any known programming language.
      Actually it is something more between a smart configurator and a programming language.
      The best way to learn it is to run gastona for desktop (gastona.jar) which comes with
      a complete documentation of the language, widgets and commands. Almost every documented element
      has one or several sample related scripts that can be modified and run immediately.
   </p>

